    <p>{`With the PagerDuty integration, each ServiceNow Configuration Item can have a corresponding PagerDuty Service. This integration offers an easy way to quickly generate a new PagerDuty service and webhook (which is necessary to send information back to ServiceNow). It will also populate the associated fields within ServiceNow.`}</p>
    <p>{`Any Configuration Item that extends the base `}<inlineCode parentName="p">{`cmdb_ci`}</inlineCode>{` table can be mapped to PagerDuty because it inherits the same field that contains the PagerDuty service ID. This makes it easy to map any type of Configuration Item to services in PagerDuty, although provisioning only Business Services, Technical Services and/or Applications is recommended. For each Configuration Item type, the form view for it will need to be modified to show the PagerDuty object ID.`}</p>
